@page
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<section class="page">
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="muted">Last updated: @DateTime.UtcNow.ToString("yyyy-MM-dd")</p>

  <h2>Who we are</h2>
  <p>OluRankings (“we”, “us”, “our”) provides youth sports rankings and verified player profiles.</p>

  <h2>Data we process</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Account data: email, password hash.</li>
    <li>Athlete data: name, age group/class year, school/club, position, stats, media links, headshot.</li>
    <li>Verification evidence: links and files submitted by users and verifiers.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Lawful basis</h2>
  <p>We process data under GDPR Art. 6(1)(b) (contract), 6(1)(f) (legitimate interests) and, for minors, consent from a parent/guardian where required.</p>

  <h2>Your rights</h2>
  <p>You can request access, rectification, objection, restriction, portability, and erasure. Contact: <a href="mailto:support@olurankings.uk">support@olurankings.uk</a>.</p>

  <h2>Retention & security</h2>
  <p>We retain the minimum necessary and secure storage with industry-standard controls. Media may be served via CDN.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Data controller: OluRankings. Email: <a href="mailto:support@olurankings.uk">support@olurankings.uk</a>.</p>
</section>
